RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Le ss Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUE GENEROUS assumed command leaving the break and dictated terms into the first turn, drew to a clear lead into the backstretch run and was well handled through moderate fractions to the half-mile marker, held a clear lead to the quarter marker, felt pressure inside of the furlong pole, dug in while all out into deep stretch, was fully extended in the final strides and gamely lasted for the win at the wire. BIG GIFT was unhurried in the early running, tracked the modest pace from a ground saving position through the backstretch run, came two wide into the far turn, was roused three wide into the drive, closed inside of the furlong marker, vied for the lead while widest nearing the sixteenth-pole, drifted in a bit inside of the sixteenth-marker and made contact with MOONSHINE CAT, surged in the final strides and just missed for the win, while just holding for the place. MOONSHINE CAT tracked the modest early pace while outside of rivals, moved up heading to the half-mile marker and ran in pursuit of SUE GENEROUS to the quarter pole, rallied nearing the furlong marker, continued that bid while between runners heading to the sixteenth-marker, was bumped by BIG GIFT in deep stretch and just missed for the win and place at the finish, while holding clearly for the show. BIG FAME lost her path at the start and was off a step slowly, stalked the modest early pace into the backstretch run, tracked the pacesetter through the backstretch run, lost ground along the far turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch and weakened in the final stages. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE RUNNING IN DEEP STRETCH. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT BIG GIFT DRIFTED IN, MADE CONTACT WITH MOONSHINE CAT AND IN DOING SO COST MOONSHINE CAT THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING. BIG GIFT WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM SECOND AND PLACED THIRD.

ENTRY.NAME: Moonshine Cat
ENTRY.OWNER: Green James C and LaGrone Selwyn

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 70. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAYS ANGEL pressed the solid early pace while outside of DANCING BONBON, drifted out a path along the turn then was steered back to the two path nearing the quarter marker, chased DANCING BONBON to mid-stretch, rallied in the final furlong, collared DANCING BONBON in deep stretch and held in a drive in the late stages. MORO FIRST CLASS chased the fast early pace while outside of rivals, was a bit hard to place while entering the turn, drifted to the four path before correcting and chased two wide to the quarter pole, ran in pursuit to mid-stretch, shifted out a path inside of the furlong marker, closed with a rush in deep stretch and missed for the win, while getting up in the final strides to secure the place. DANCING BONBON was forwardly placed leaving the break and was sent to establish the early lead, set solid fractions while pressured into the turn, extended the lead along the bend while drifting out a bit nearing the quarter marker, was steered back to the rail and drew to a clear lead at mid-stretch, was kept to task while holding safely to the sixteenth-marker, was collared by the winner in deep stretch and was just edged for the place, while holding clearly for the show. JERSEY BIRD chased the solid early pace from the inside, improved position on the turn, ran evenly to the furlong marker and lacked a final response. RIVIERA SUNRISE chased the solid early pace from the rear, was outrun along the turn, trailed into the drive and did not threaten. WESTERN TOWN broke alertly and was prominent in the early stages, pressed the pace while outside of rivals into the turn, lost ground while four then three wide nearing the quarter marker, was outrun to mid-stretch and gave way in the final stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EL BERRINCHES assumed command leaving the break, set decent fractions while off of the rail through the turn and was pressed to the quarter marker, shook free into upper stretch, was kept to task under steady late urging and held safely for the win in the final stages. HUMBLEBUMBLEFUMBLE raced wide early, chased outside of the leading pair into the turn, improved position while three wide along the bend and pressed EL BERRINCHES to the quarter marker, lost ground to that rival into upper stretch, drifted out through the lane and was unable to muster the needed late response, while holding for the place. G'S LAST CHANCE hopped at the break and was off a step slowly, recovered to stalk the moderate early pace from the inside, pressed the pace while inside of rivals along the turn, lost ground into upper stretch, weakened in the final furlong and was outfinished for the place.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OAT MILK LATTE was allowed to settle, tracked the decent pace through the backstretch run while outside of an inner rival, shifted to the four path along the far turn and improved position nearing the quarter marker, was asked for run in upper stretch, chased HAPPY IS to the furlong marker, overtook that rival inside of the sixteenth-marker and held in a drive over the oncoming runner-up. ZAFFERANA was unhurried while saving ground in the early stages, moved to the three path approaching the quarter marker, swung widest into upper stretch and mounted a five wide bid into the drive, finished well in the final sixteenth, pressured the winner in deep stretch but could not get by OAT MILK LATTE in the final strides and bested the rest. AMANDA ROSE hopped at the start and was off a step slowly, was a bit rank in the early stages and pulled on the rider while three wide into the first turn, was content to trail through the backstretch run, chased two wide along the far turn, came five wide into the stretch, shifted out a path at mid-stretch and raced widest into the final furlong, closed willingly in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to secure the show. HAPPY IS was sent to be forwardly placed in the early running, contested the pace with WHATWASTHENISNOW into the first turn, shook free along the backstretch run and set decent fractions to the half-mile marker, came under pressure again from WHATWASTHENISNOW nearing the quarter marker, repelled that bid and extended the lead at the furlong grounds, was all out approaching the sixteenth-marker, could not hold off oncoming rivals in the final stages and faltered, while just being edged for the show. BIG JOLT stalked the decent early pace from the inside, maintained her position through the backstretch run while well placed, gave chase while saving ground along the far turn, made a mild gain at the furlong marker but could not sustain that run into deep stretch and lacked a final response. WHATWASTHENISNOW broke alertly, contested the early pace with HAPPY IS while outside of that rival into the first turn, attended to the pace along the backstretch run then pressed HAPPY IS along the far turn, was turned away heading into the stretch drive and weakened in the late going. ELEGANCE CODE settled in mid-pack while saving ground, saved all of the ground to the far turn, made a mild gain at the furlong marker but could not sustain that run in the final stages and did not threaten. HERSABIGGIRL settled outside of rivals along the first turn, gained ground along the backstretch run, mounted a three wide bid along the far turn, could not keep pace into the drive, weakened in the final furlong and did not factor. NOBLE HEARTED was forwardly placed into the first turn, tracked the decent pace while off of the rail through the backstretch run, was well placed while two wide and between runners approaching the second turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, failed to respond to firm urging in the drive and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNION COACH showed good early speed leaving the break, contested the solid pace while outside of a rival into the turn, came in a bit while outside of BIG CATTY and crowded that rival midway through the turn, took command nearing the quarter marker and extended the lead into upper stretch, responded to urging inside of the furlong marker and drew clear in the final stages in a good debut. STREET TIGER chased the solid early pace, maintained a two wide path to the quarter marker, raced three wide into the stretch and made a mild gain at the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and just held for the place. CRYPTO CRUSH chased the solid early pace while outside of rivals, lost ground while three wide on the turn, chased into the stretch, raced widest into the final furlong, closed in deep stretch and just missed for the place, while getting up in time to secure the show. BIG CATTY was prominent in the early running and pressed the decent pace while inside of UNION COACH, was bothered a bit by that rival along the turn and steadied while in tight nearing the quarter marker, lost position nearing the top of the stretch, gave chase to the furlong grounds, weakened in the final stages and was outfinished for the show. CANDY LITZ chased the decent early pace while widest into the turn, raced four then three wide into the bend and lost ground nearing the quarter marker, lacked a response in the stretch and did not threaten. ABOVE THE FOLD lacked early speed, saved ground into the turn and made a mild gain nearing the quarter marker, tipped two wide for the stretch run and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 6 5F Turf CR: 82. Starter Allowance Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when determinin g eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WESTWARD BREEZE was off a step slowly, settled while saving ground into the turn, made a mild gain nearing the quarter marker, was guided to the outside and swung widest for the drive, improved position at the furlong grounds, closed with a rush in the final sixteenth, came within aim in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to prevail. HARBOR'S ROSE was forwardly placed in the early stages then rated off of the fast pace into the turn, chased the decent pace while two wide along the bend, tipped three wide for the drive and closed to come within aim at the furlong marker, overtook BLUEBERRY MUFFIN in deep stretch to take command, was just nipped on the wire for the win and held for the place in a good effort. SWEET LAYLA RAE tracked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, gained ground while three wide on the turn, maintained that three wide path into the stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, closed fast in deep stretch, vied for the lead in the final strides and just missed for the win and place, while getting up in time to secure the show. BLUEBERRY MUFFIN showed good early speed, disputed the solid pace while outside of rivals into the turn, took a narrow lead while two wide along the bend, battled with ANNA'S MUSIC to the furlong marker, shook free then was caught by HARBOR'S ROSE inside of the sixteenth-marker, could not hold off oncoming rivals in the final strides and was outfinished. ANNA'S MUSIC was prominent in the early running and pressed the pace while inside of BLUEBERRY MUFFIN, pressed the decent pace to the quarter marker, saved ground to the top of the lane and battled with BLUEBERRY MUFFIN to mid-stretch, could not keep pace into the final stages and weakened. ASSUREDLY chased the early pace then took back approaching the turn, came two wide to the quarter marker, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch and did not mount a late rally. BET DE VRON bobbled at the start, recovered to be prominent in the early running and raced close to the decent early pace, chased from the rail along the turn, checked while in tight nearing the quarter marker, lost position into the stretch and faded. TWO TWELVE was fractious prior to the start, raced in tight quarters in the opening furlong, steadied and was shuffled back heading to the half-mile marker, recovered and chased outside of rivals into the turn, raced within aim while two wide nearing the quarter marker, swung four wide for the drive, was outrun to mid-stretch and tired in the final stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Luther Burbank S. SANTA ROSA RACE 7 1 1/16M Turf CR: 98. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. By subscription of $50 each which shall accompany the nomination, or by supplementary nomination of $1,250 (includes all fees) made by time of entries. $500 to enter. With $75,000 Guaranteed with $45,000 to the winner, $15,000 to second, $9,000 to third, $4,500 to fourth and $1,500 to fifth. Weight Three Year Olds 122 lbs. Older 125 lbs. Non winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs. Non winners of a race other than maiden, claiming or starter allowed 4 lbs. Closed Monday, July 31, 2023 with 14 nominations. High weights preferred.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASCENDANCY took back off of the early pace and tracked while outside of a rival into the first turn, advanced along the backstretch run, continued that gain into the far turn and was given her cue while three wide nearing the quarter marker, rallied in mid-stretch and confronted EVER SMART approaching the furlong grounds, responded to urging and took command into the final sixteenth, put away EVER SMART in deep stretch and drove clear in the end. EVER SMART was prominent in the early running and stalked the pace while three wide along the first turn, advanced position along the backstretch run and prompted the pace to the half-mile marker, confronted the pacesetter along the second turn and took command approaching the top of the lane, was set down in upper stretch and was confronted by ASCENDANCY at the furlong grounds, met that bid to the sixteenth-pole but could not hold off the winner in the final stages and was outfinished, while holding for the place. ASSIGNATION was unhurried in the early running, saved all of the ground through the backstretch run, came in tight while along the rail nearing the three-furlong marker and shifted two wide into the far turn, gained ground at the quarter pole, came two then three wide into the stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, shifted four wide into deep stretch, closed well in the final stages and just won the nod on the wire for the show. UNDISTURBED stalked the decent early pace from the inside, tracked the leaders while outside of a rival through the backstretch run, gained ground along the far turn while two wide, was steered four wide into upper stretch, lost position at the furlong marker, finished evenly in the final stages and just missed for the show. CLOCKSTRIKESTWELVE settled along the rail in the early running, was well placed through the backstretch run, saved all of the ground to the quarter marker, made a mild gain into upper stretch, lacked the needed response in the final furlong and was outkicked in deep stretch. MADEIRA WINE was sent to establish the early lead, set decent fractions while on a clear lead into the backstretch run, showed the way to the half-mile pole while carving out a solid pace, was confronted along the second turn and was overtaken nearing the quarter marker, chased to the furlong pole and faded in the final stages. COUNCILWOMAN JILLY broke in the air at the start and spotted the field in the early stages, trailed to the second turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch and passed tiring rivals late but did not threaten. BELLEO'S FOREST settled in the second flight while outside of a rival in the early going, lugged out and raced four to five wide along the bend then recovered into the backstretch run, maintained her position to the half-mile marker, made a mild gain while three wide along the far turn, could not sustain that run into the stretch and did not factor in the late stages. TAM'S LITTLE ANGEL was forwardly placed while two wide in the early stages, stalked the decent pace through the backstretch run, lost ground heading to the quarter marker and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELCONDOR was sent hard from the start quickly angled over to the rail, gained the early advantage then was clear of the field by the half mile pole, held sway through the turn with four rivals in close pursuit, came into the stretch in the three path then veered sharply to the six path at the top of the stretch, had enough left to fend off a fast closing MY BUCKET LIST and just lasted. MY BUCKET LIST stumbled slightly at the break then was carried out very wide when DRAW SOME impeded his path after the break, altered course to the inside then raced three to four wide throughout, tipped out to the five path for the stretch run and rallied nicely to just miss despite being carried out some in mid-stretch when MISCHIEVOUS PIRATE altered course. MISCHIEVOUS PIRATE came away well despite some contact with LUCKY DIABLO from the outside, contested the early pace, checked briefly down the backstretch run when ELCONDOR cut across his path, then moved out a path to re-engage the leaders going into the turn, had to alter course at the top of the stretch to avoid ELCONDOR once again when that one veered out, ran on to the finish but could not find another gear when needed in the late stages. BEGIN AGAIN stumbled at the break then while off-balance bumped hard into LUCKY DIABLO, recovered, then made some steady forward progress on the leaders to move into serious contention by the three eighths marker, stayed to the inside through the turn and entered the stretch with a chance and finished up well but was not quite enough to crack the top three. NORDIC SEA got a clean break then was not pressed for speed and was outrun down the backstretch, kept to task with encouragement from the rider and managed to pass a few in the final furlong. WESTERN SIERRA broke well then set out to contest the early pace, got put in a bit tight near the seven-sixteenths marker then shifted out out a path but was then forced to duel between horses while in tight quarters going into the turn then dropped back off the pace near the quarter pole and was unable to recover from there. DRAW SOME ducked out after the break and bothered MY BUCKET LIST, raced three wide and in the middle of the pack early on, struggled to keep up with the pace from the turn and struggled home running one-paced to the finish. MISCHIEF'S THIRSTY ducked in sharply at the start, saved ground and came under heavy pressure early but was unable to make an impact. LUCKY DIABLO got pinballed into MISCHIEVOUS PIRATE when bumped hard by BEGIN AGAIN from the outside at the start, steadied, then fell well behind the field and trailed throughout. THERE WAS A JOCKEY'S OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF MISCHIEVOUS PIRATE AGAINST THE RIDER OF ELCONDOR FOR THE INCIDENT IN UPPER TO MID-STRETCH. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THE OBJECTION WOULD NOT BE ALLOWED AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.
